A developer tries to add the Python language override block but VS Code shows a JSON parsing error and the settings are not applied:

```jsonc
{
  "python.defaultInterpreterPath": "/opt/anaconda3/bin/python",
  "editor.renderWhitespace": "all"
  "[python]": {
    "editor.codeActionsOnSave": {
      "source.organizeImports": "explicit"
    }
  }
}
```

1) Identify the exact syntax issue.
2) Provide the corrected snippet (only the minimal fix).

questions.correct_answer:
1) The comma is missing after the line `"editor.renderWhitespace": "all"`.

2)
```jsonc
{
  "python.defaultInterpreterPath": "/opt/anaconda3/bin/python",
  "editor.renderWhitespace": "all",
  "[python]": {
    "editor.codeActionsOnSave": {
      "source.organizeImports": "explicit"
    }
  }
}
```

questions.question_text:
In VS Code, you want to add language-specific settings for Python to your User Settings JSON. Which of the following correctly adds a new top-level `[python]` block to an existing settings file?

A)
```jsonc
{
  "editor.renderWhitespace": "all"
  "[python]": {
    "editor.codeActionsOnSave": {
      "source.organizeImports": "explicit"
    }
  }
}
```

B)
```jsonc
{
  "editor.renderWhitespace": "all",
  "[python]": {
    "editor.codeActionsOnSave": {
      "source.organizeImports": "explicit"
    }
  }
}
```

C)
```jsonc
{
  "editor.renderWhitespace": "all",
  "python": {
    "editor.codeActionsOnSave": {
      "source.organizeImports": "explicit"
    }
  }
}
```

D)
```jsonc
{
  "editor.renderWhitespace": "all",
  "[python]": [
    "editor.codeActionsOnSave",
    "source.organizeImports=explicit"
  ]
}
```

